./specs/t-040@20260416t181925z-spec.md:65:budget enforcement, and startup `bootstrap_identity`. These are all out of
./CHANGELOG.md:34:- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
./CHANGELOG.md:45:- Locked the EMSD room sampler to tracker transport: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits `transport_trigger_now` / `transport_trigger_key`, `sample_playback_engine.py` uses those keys to launch once per musical bucket instead of only by cooldown, and the face/status layer can now reflect that transport-synchronized sampler execution.
./CHANGELOG.md:47:- Fixed the remaining live self-monitor blackout path: when direct `jack_rec` capture times out, `self_listener.py` now falls back to analyzing a fresh `/tmp/room_capture.wav` clip instead of writing a dark `capture_timeout` state, so glyph and sampler decisions stay audio-derived on boxes where the JACK recorder hangs.
./CHANGELOG.md:51:- Added a replayable musical integration regression that exercises the composer-state -> sampler-plan -> sample-playback -> self-listener glyph state -> face-status chain, so this integration can be verified without a live host.
./CHANGELOG.md:62:- Made the cold-boot meter less ambiguous: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now chooses `SELF_LISTENER_CAPTURE_BACKEND` from the boot-time graph decision, preferring a live PipeWire sink monitor before JACK fallbacks, and it performs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start room/sampler/face daemons from other boot hooks are collapsed back to one process each.
./CHANGELOG.md:67:- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.
./CHANGELOG.md:72:- Tightened head-monitor truth again: the sample status line can now read `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` and show actual live sampler playback instead of only the planned source/mode.
./CHANGELOG.md:73:- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
./CHANGELOG.md:78:- Rebased the EMSD ambient default onto the real room condenser path: Divination/capstone planning and DSP source focus now prefer `room_mic` instead of `garden_mic`, so the default ambient sampler matches the Perform-VE microphone actually present on CypherClaw.
./CHANGELOG.md:81:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
