./sdp/runner.log:1114:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-25T19:21:58.221Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777144918221_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-002 @20260425T183959Zb\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-25\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`\n- `tests/test_sampler_effects.py`\n- `my-claw/supercollider/test_sampler_effects.scd`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of the `sw_sampler_fx` SynthDef correctly follows the requirements.\n- It uses `PartConv.ar` for convolution reverb and `FreeVerb.ar` as a fallback.\n- The IR buffer presence check `BufFrames.kr(ir_bufnum) > 0` correctly gates the branches.\n- A guarded bufnum (`safeIRBuf`) ensures `PartConv` is not fed an invalid sentinel like -1.\n- The signal chain follows the specified order: delay -> reverb -> freeze -> comb.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete.\n- Both reverb branches are implemented and switchable at runtime based on IR buffer presence.\n- Python tests in `tests/test_sampler_effects.py` provide thorough static verification of the SCD source logic.\n- An SC-side runtime test `my-claw/supercollider/test_sampler_effects.scd` verifies the comb filter and non-silent output.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation is consistent with the established patterns in the codebase, using standard SuperCollider UGens and idiomatic Python testing for SCD source code.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues identified. The use of `Select.kr` to guard bufnums prevents potential SuperCollider UGen errors with invalid buffer indices.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-commented and the tests are exhaustive for the scope of the task. The use of `SelectX.ar` for clean switching between reverb branches is a good design choice.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The Python static tests are particularly impressive for ensuring the SCD source logic matches the requirements without requiring a local SuperCollider installation for every test run.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-002 @20260425t183959zb-verify.md"}}
