./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:2:**Source:** `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md`
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:13:This PRD adds a fifth signature voice — **`sw_sampler`** — that elevates the room itself, the artist's recorded history, and a curated found-sound library into a primary instrument. The sampler is **how CypherClaw metabolizes the room**: it listens continuously to the contact mic and room mic, captures fragments worth remembering, and replays those fragments granularly — stretched, transposed, scrubbed, with a dedicated effects bus — back into the live performance.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:25:1. **Granular by default, never one-shot.** The sampler is a granular voice with grain size 20–200 ms, density, position scrub, and pitch transpose. "Press button hear sample" is not a use case. Every play is a re-rendering through grains.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:29:5. **Restraint earned, not eroded.** The sampler joins the quartet to make a quintet, but it does not relax the 3-voice base / 2-voice deliberate / 4-voice climax discipline. Heavy sampler use replaces, not adds. In *Solitary* mode the sampler may be the *only* voice.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:35:**In scope:** a granular SuperCollider voice (`sw_sampler`) with a dedicated effects bus; a sample library on disk with tag-based selection; a continuous live-capture daemon for contact/room mics; a self-quotation loop; integration with the existing artist-mode selector and cast planner so the sampler joins the signature quintet; metrics and anti-pattern detection for sampler over- or under-use.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:39:- Full DAW-style multi-track sampler with chopping, slicing, or loop-point editing UI. The sampler is a granular voice, not a workstation.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:41:- Replacement of any existing signature voice. The quartet stays; the sampler is added to make a quintet.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:48:**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCS-001..CCS-008).** Sample data model, on-disk library layout, tag taxonomy, mood/mode-aware selector, character-registry entry for `voice_sampler`, signature-voice quintet update. Pure Python + tests. At end of phase, the selector picks plausible samples for any (mode, arc, mood) tuple from a library of stub/placeholder files; no audio plays yet.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:50:**Phase 2 — SuperCollider granular voice (CCS-009..CCS-014).** `sw_sampler.scd` SynthDef with grain-controlled buffer playback; buffer-management protocol for loading samples on demand; dedicated effects bus (delay + reverb + spectral freeze + comb-to-B); mix-engine integration so the sampler routes through the master bus. End of phase: sending OSC `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=N grain_size=80ms density=12 pitch=0` plays a granular cloud audible through the speakers.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:54:**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:56:**Phase 5 — Verification + observability (CCS-029..CCS-033).** Per-piece sampler-event metrics; anti-pattern detection for sampler dominating (over-quote) or never appearing (silent quintet member); a sample-usage journal that records which samples played in which pieces with what transformations; end-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw confirming the daemon is capturing, the selector is choosing, the synth is playing, and the self-listener is observing the right output peaks. End of phase: composer can demonstrate a piece that uses 1 self-quotation + 1 room-capture + 1 library sample, all selector-chosen, all routed through the effects bus, all surfaced in the diagnostics dashboard.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:60:- `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md` — the rendering layer; sampler events flow through the same RenderPass (R-rules respect `role="sampler"` with grid_locked=False so phrasing applies, but R8 microtiming is dampened on grain-time-scale events).
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:61:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` — Mode-driven voice/tempo/density. `SIGNATURE_VOICES` extends from quartet to quintet; modes specify per-mode sampler density.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:62:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` — `select_cast_ids` already supports `preferred_synths` and `voice_count_target`; the sampler joins the cast through this same path.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:63:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py` and `mix_engine.py` — the sampler effects bus routes its summed output through the master, respecting amp/compression caps.
./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:64:- Existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/` directory and `boot_synthdefs.scd` — `sw_sampler.scsyndef` joins the boot-time SynthDef load.
