./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6879:- **Details:** Local verification passed after the provider-model escalation, but `sdp-cli tasks manual-verify` could not record the result because an active `sdp-cli run` process (PID 69939) owns `.sdp/run.lock`. The lock was not removed. Candidate hardening was checked explicitly: both startup entrypoints call `bootstrap_identity()` before `FirstBootAnnouncer`, and `pytest tests/test_first_boot.py tests/test_governor_integration.py -q` passed. No new dependencies were added.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6884:- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`, which belong to the federation/identity subsystem. This task (installation-aware acoustic ecology policies) has no relation to the startup identity flow. The new module `acoustic_ecology.py` is a pure-function policy layer with no I/O and no state files — it cannot affect startup sequencing. No new dependencies required; stdlib only.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6889:- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`, which belong to the federation/identity subsystem. This task (artistic identity portfolio reporting) has no relation to the startup identity flow. The new module `portfolio_report.py` is a pure-function reporting layer with no I/O and no state files — it derives summaries from data passed to it and cannot affect startup sequencing. No new dependencies required; stdlib only.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6894:- **Details:** This task adds stdlib-only SenseWeave diagnostics and environment-backed feature flags; no new dependencies are required. The candidate startup hardening items remain covered by the existing startup flow: both daemon entrypoints call `bootstrap_identity()` before `FirstBootAnnouncer`, and `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` plus `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` were re-run as regression anchors.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6914:- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity`, `FirstBootAnnouncer` (federation/identity subsystem), and resource governor budget enforcement (resource_governor.py). This task adds dissonance/resolution metadata to `counterpoint_rules.py` — a pure-function analysis layer with no I/O, no state files, and no interaction with startup sequencing or resource budgets. The `revise_score()` pipeline integration hardening item is already addressed: `revise_score` is imported and called in both `tracker_compiler.py` (line 18/1357) and `duet_composer.py` (line 80/838). No new dependencies required; stdlib only.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6919:- **Details:** This task turns the production-course curriculum into executable exercise metadata and generated scaffolds. The auto-generated hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer` belong to the startup identity subsystem and are already addressed in the current tree: both `my-claw/tools/daemon.py` and `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` call `bootstrap_identity()` before `FirstBootAnnouncer`, while `tests/test_first_boot.py` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py` cover persistence and wiring for standalone/federated startup paths. No new dependencies or migrations are required.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6951:- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6962:- Locked the EMSD room sampler to tracker transport: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits `transport_trigger_now` / `transport_trigger_key`, `sample_playback_engine.py` uses those keys to launch once per musical bucket instead of only by cooldown, and the face/status layer can now reflect that transport-synchronized sampler execution.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6964:- Fixed the remaining live self-monitor blackout path: when direct `jack_rec` capture times out, `self_listener.py` now falls back to analyzing a fresh `/tmp/room_capture.wav` clip instead of writing a dark `capture_timeout` state, so glyph and sampler decisions stay audio-derived on boxes where the JACK recorder hangs.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6968:- Added a replayable musical integration regression that exercises the composer-state -> sampler-plan -> sample-playback -> self-listener glyph state -> face-status chain, so this integration can be verified without a live host.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6979:- Made the cold-boot meter less ambiguous: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now chooses `SELF_LISTENER_CAPTURE_BACKEND` from the boot-time graph decision, preferring a live PipeWire sink monitor before JACK fallbacks, and it performs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start room/sampler/face daemons from other boot hooks are collapsed back to one process each.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6984:- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6989:- Tightened head-monitor truth again: the sample status line can now read `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` and show actual live sampler playback instead of only the planned source/mode.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6990:- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6995:- Rebased the EMSD ambient default onto the real room condenser path: Divination/capstone planning and DSP source focus now prefer `room_mic` instead of `garden_mic`, so the default ambient sampler matches the Perform-VE microphone actually present on CypherClaw.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:6998:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
