sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:890:class TestAblate:
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1515:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:75:| CCH-001 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1516:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:76:| CCH-002 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1517:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:77:| CCH-003 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1520:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:80:| CCH-006 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | MUST | T1 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1525:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:86:| CCH-012 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1526:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:87:| CCH-013 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1527:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:88:| CCH-014 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1528:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:89:| CCH-015 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1529:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:90:| CCH-016 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1530:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:91:| CCH-017 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1531:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:92:| CCH-018 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1532:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:93:| CCH-019 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1535:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:96:| CCH-022 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1536:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:97:| CCH-023 | Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/silence_budget.py` maintains rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density)·dt per voice<br/>- when rest_budget exceeds threshold at phrase boundary, either extends breath (via R6) or drops next phrase to tacet<br/>- tests verify accumulator math, threshold trigger, and tacet-drop path |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1537:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:99:| CCH-025 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1539:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:103:| CCH-029 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | MUST | T1 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1540:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:104:| CCH-030 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260416T181925Z_1776387613.log:1543:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:110:| CCH-036 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | MUST | T1 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via scipy.spatial.ConvexHull<br/>- reject point-worm (mechanical: area < 1.0) and space-filling worm (random: area > saturation threshold)<br/>- CI attaches worm PNGs to build artifacts for listener review |
