-024 | Define `SampleRecord` dataclass with sample-id, path, source, character tags, pitch, duration, captured-at, arc context, RMS, peak, transient density. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-001 | T-001 | - `sample_library.SampleRecord` defined with fields: `sample_id` (UUID), `path` (Path), `source` (Literal['library','self','room','contact','theramini','keyboard']), `character_tags` (frozenset[str]), `pitch_hz` (float &#124; None), `pitch_confidence` (float), `duration_sec` (float), `captured_at` (datetime), `arc_phase` (str &#124; None), `mood` (dict[str,float] &#124; None), `presence` (Literal['present','none','unknown'] &#124; None), `rms` (float), `peak` (float), `transient_density` (float), `gain_db` (float, default 0.0)<br/>- dataclass is frozen and JSON-serializable; ISO-8601 timestamp round-trip<br/>- tests verify schema, defaults, JSON round-trip, and rejection of out-of-range values |\n+| 25 | T-025 | Define controlled `CHARACTER_TAGS` vocabulary (warm, metallic, wind, pulse, voice, mechanical, water, sustained, transient, percussive, harmonic, noisy). | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-002 | T-001 | - `sample_library.CHARACTER_TAGS` is a frozenset of exactly the 12 listed tags<br/>- `SampleRecord.character_tags` validation rejects unknown tags<br/>- tests verify rejection path and the canonical 12-tag set |\n+| 26 | T-026 | Implement `SampleLibrary` on-disk store backed by `index.sqlite` with tag/source/pitch/mood-range queries. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-003 | T-001 | - `SampleLibrary(root: Path)` opens / creates `index.sqlite` with table `samples` carrying every `SampleRecord` field plus full-text-search index on `character_tags`<br/>- `library.add(record)` persists row + verifies file presence<br/>- `library.find(source=, character_any=, character_all=, pitch_band=, arc_phase=, mood_range=, limit=)` returns ordered list (most recent first within match set)<br/>- tests cover insert, query by each filter, empty-result path, and corrupted-DB rebuild |\n+| 27 | T-027 | Define on-disk directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/` with `library/`, `self/`, `room/`, `contact/`, `theramini/`, `keyboard/` subdirs and `index.sqlite`. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCS-004 | T-001 | - `SampleLibrary.bootstrap(root)` creates the six subdirectories + `index.sqlite` if missing, idempotent<br/>- documented as the canonical layout in module docstring<br/>- tests verify bootstrap on tmp dir creates all six subdirs and the SQLite file |\n+| 28 | T-028 | Implement `SampleSelector` mood/mode/arc-aware picker with deterministic seed-based selection within match set. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-005 | T-001 | - `SampleSelector(library, rng_seed: int)` exposes `select(mode: ArtistMode, arc_phase: str, mood: Mapping[str,float], target_character: tuple[str,...] = (), avoid_recent: int = 5) -> SampleRecord &#124; None`<br/>- selection prefers samples with matching `arc_phase` and overlapping mood (dot-product over energy/valence/arousal); falls back to character_tags only; falls back to library random within source-source preference per-mode<br/>- `avoid_recent` excludes the N most-recently-played samples (per-mode rolling window)<br/>- per-mode source preference: solitary→[self,contact,room,library]; companion→[library,self,room]; working_ambience→[room,library]; evening_reflection→[self,library,theramini]; storm→[contact,library,room]<br/>- selection is deterministic given (library state, rng_seed, kwargs)<br/>- tests verify per-mode preference order, mood-overlap ranking, avoid_recent, deterministic replay |\n+| 29 | T-029 | Add `sw_sampler` to `SIGNATURE_VOICES` quintet in `artist_identity.py` and update `VOICE_ROLES` so a `\"sampler\"` role maps to `\"sw_sampler\"`. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-006 | T-001 | - `SIGNATURE_VOICES` becomes `(\"sw_bell_warm\", \"sw_bowed\", \"sw_breath\", \"sw_pad\", \"sw_sampler\")`<br/>- `VOICE_ROLES[\"sampler\"] = \"sw_sampler\"`<br/>- existing `VOICE_ROLES` keys for melody/counter/color/texture/bass unchanged<br/>- existing `test_artist_identity.py::TestSi