sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959za-verify.md:35:The code is clean, well-commented, and includes a comprehensive test suite (`tests/test_sampler_buffers.py`) that covers edge cases like stereo files and missing WAVs. The tests use a clean mock OSC client.
sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959za-verify.md:38:- [ ] **Minor — Redundant OSC Command**: `/b_alloc` is technically redundant when followed by `/b_allocRead`, as the latter performs allocation. However, this follows the literal wording of the spec and is not harmful.
sdp/logs/Verify_T-038_20260416T181925Z_1776445321.log:149:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-17T17:02:54.909Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1776445372437_0","status":"success","output":"diff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md\nindex 9e072ff..e721a25 100644\n--- a/CHANGELOG.md\n+++ b/CHANGELOG.md\n@@ -2,6 +2,7 @@\n \n ## Unreleased\n \n+- Coupled narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection: new `narrative_envelope.py` module maps procedural arc state (phase, density, dynamic, timbre) and section function into populated SectionEnvelope instances with phase-shaped tension trajectories, tone-derived brightness and dynamic planes, and arc-driven density targets. `compose_score_tree()` now produces non-default section envelopes on every section node, so dramatic arcs drive section-level musical parameters instead of using flat defaults.\n - Added the core SenseWeave render-ablation API: `senseweave.render.ablation.ablate()` now filters selected active render rule IDs, preserves remaining rule order, rerenders through an injected renderer, rejects unknown disabled IDs, and exposes a default no-rule path through the existing score-to-frequency renderer for future humanization tooling.\n - Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to \"unavailable\" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.\n - Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.\ndiff --git a/ESCALATIONS.md b/ESCALATIONS.md\nindex 461096d..0a939d5 100644\n--- a/ESCALATIONS.md\n+++ b/ESCALATIONS.md\n@@ -175,3 +175,8 @@ reasoning effor...\n \n - **Reason:** Agent timeout\n - **Details:** T-021@20260416T181925Z timed out twice. Run sdp-cli tasks split T-021@20260416T181925Z to break it down.\n+\n+## T-038@20260416T181925Z (2026-04-17T00:00:00+00:00)\n+\n+- **Reason:** Candidate hardening items are out of scope\n+- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity`, `FirstBootAnnouncer` (startup identity subsystem), resource governor budget enforcement, and `revise_score` pipeline integration. This task couples the narrative engine (procedural arc) to SectionEnvelope selection — a pure-function mapping layer with no I/O, no state files, and no interaction with startup sequencing, resource budgets, or the self-critique pipeline. The `revise_score()` integration is already addressed in both `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py`. No new dependencies or migrations are required.\ndiff --git a/my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py b/my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py\nindex 73c45e1..7e3031d 100644\n--- a/my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py\n+++ b/my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py\n@@ -16,9 +16,9 @@ from .score_tree import (\n     PerformanceIntent,\n     PhraseNode,\n     ScoreTree,\n-    SectionEnvelope,\n     SectionNode,\n )\n+from cypherclaw.render.narrative_envelope import beat_from_directive, envelope_for_beat\n \n \n _INTENT_BY_FUNCTION: dict[str, str] = {\n@@ -67,11 +67,12 @@ def _production_arc_for_sections(\n     *,\n     commission: 