     1	"""Sampler buffer loading for the cypherclaw scsynth backend.
     2	
     3	`BufferLoader.on_sampler_load(record)` allocates an scsynth buffer via
     4	`/b_alloc` (sized from the WAV header), reads the WAV file into it via
     5	`/b_allocRead`, and stores the assigned buffer id back on the record.
     6	`BufferLoader.on_sampler_free(record)` releases the buffer via `/b_free`
     7	and clears the id; calling it on a record without a live buffer is a
     8	no-op so callers can free idempotently.
     9	
    10	Live records are tracked in an LRU ordering: loads and `touch(record)`
    11	mark a record most-recently-used, and once the live set exceeds
    12	`capacity` the least-recently-used record is auto-freed on the next
    13	load.
    14	"""
