     1	# Specification: T-001@20260425T183959Zd
     2	
     3	## Problem Statement
     4	
     5	`BufferLoader` already supports `on_sampler_load()`, `on_sampler_free()`, and
     6	basic LRU bookkeeping, but the capacity-overflow path is still implemented by a
     7	private `_evict_lru()` helper that duplicates the release logic instead of
     8	reusing the public free path. That leaves the cap enforcement logic slightly
     9	out of sync with the contract implied by the task graph: when the 64-buffer cap
    10	is reached, the least-recently-used live record should be evicted through the
    11	same release path used by explicit frees before a new buffer is allocated.
    12	
    13	The current tests also only exercise small-capacity eviction in unit-style
    14	scenarios. There is no regression test that fills the default-capacity pool and
    15	proves the full load/evict cycle works end to end.
    16	
    17	## Technical Approach
    18	
    19	Keep the existing `BufferLoader` interface and OSC behavior, but tighten the
    20	eviction path.
    21	
    22	1. Add fail-fast capacity validation in `BufferLoader.__init__()` so invalid
    23	   `capacity < 1` configurations raise `ValueError`, matching the nearby
    24	   `MotifMemory` fixed-capacity pattern.
    25	2. Replace the private overflow-only eviction shortcut with a public
    26	   `evict_lru()` helper that:
    27	   - finds the oldest tracked record
    28	   - delegates the actual release and bookkeeping to `on_sampler_free(record)`
    29	   - returns the evicted record (or `None` when nothing is tracked)
    30	3. Update `on_sampler_load()` so when `len(self._lru) >= self.capacity`, it
    31	   calls `evict_lru()` before allocating the new buffer.
    32	4. Add a regression test that:
    33	   - fills the loader to the default 64-buffer capacity
    34	   - triggers a 65th load
    35	   - asserts the oldest record is evicted
    36	   - asserts eviction happens through `on_sampler_free()`
    37	   - asserts `/b_free` is sent before the new `/b_alloc` and `/b_allocRead`
    38	
    39	## Edge Cases
    40	
    41	- `capacity=0` or any negative capacity should raise `ValueError` at
    42	  construction time instead of failing later with `KeyError`.
    43	- `evict_lru()` should return `None` when no live records are tracked.
    44	- Explicit free behavior must remain idempotent and continue removing the freed
    45	  record from LRU accounting.
    46	- Touch-based LRU promotion must keep working after the eviction path is
    47	  rerouted through `on_sampler_free()`.
    48	
    49	## Assumptions
    50	
    51	- This split task continues the existing `BufferLoader` implementation rather
    52	  than renaming it to `BufferPool`; the public behavior is the priority in this
    53	  slice.
    54	- The "integration test" requirement is satisfied by a filesystem-backed,
    55	  multi-record pytest that exercises the real loader code path with mocked OSC
    56	  sends rather than a live scsynth process.
    57	- The auto-generated startup hardening checks are out of scope for this task
    58	  because sampler buffer management does not participate in daemon startup or
    59	  identity bootstrapping.
    60	- No new third-party dependencies or database migrations are required.
    61	
    62	## Acceptance Criteria
    63	
    64	1. When `on_sampler_load()` is called with the default 64-buffer cap already
    65	   full, the least-recently-used record is evicted before allocating the new
    66	   buffer, and the eviction is routed through `on_sampler_free()`.
    67	   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_sampler_buffers.py::test_on_sampler_load_evicts_lru_via_on_sampler_free_at_default_capacity -q`
    68	
    69	2. LRU promotion semantics remain intact after the eviction path is rerouted.
    70	   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_sampler_buffers.py::test_touch_promotes_record_to_most_recently_used -q`
    71	
    72	3. Invalid non-positive capacities fail fast with `ValueError`.
    73	   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_sampler_buffers.py::test_buffer_loader_requires_positive_capacity -q`
    74	
